data.name: FilenameTsmi.ToolTipText
data.value: WPL supports a "playlist title" separate from the file name (shown as the playlist name on Windows Media Player). When loading playlists, WPLConverter either uses the filename for M3U(8) files, or the "title" attribute on WPL files. Check this to instead use the filename of the file you're saving as the "title" attribute.

data.name: TrackInfoTsmi.ToolTipText
data.value: M3U(8) files support extra metadata for each track, normally containing the track's length and a "display title". Since WPLConverter can't read track metadata it normally doesn't include any, but you can check this option to include the track's filename as the display title and - since we can't read track length - 0 length.
